00:39:38.410 --> 00:39:43.450
as an idea of what
we can do as writers.

00:39:43.450 --> 00:39:48.330
So I -- I read a couple of poems
written in different personas.

00:39:48.330 --> 00:39:53.800
This poem is -- it's
based on a slave narrative

00:39:53.800 --> 00:39:56.580
that was published in 1798.

00:39:56.580 --> 00:40:01.890 position:56%
It's the narrative of the life of
Venture Smith who was born in Guinea

00:40:01.890 --> 00:40:09.870
in 1729 and was captured as a
child, brought to North America,

00:40:09.870 --> 00:40:14.190
served for about 30 years
in slavery in Connecticut,

00:40:14.190 --> 00:40:16.860
New York, and Rhode Island.

00:40:16.860 --> 00:40:20.800
And -- so what I -- what I
did is write a book based

00:40:20.800 --> 00:40:26.050
on Venture's narrative, so it's a
-- it's a slave narrative in verse.

00:40:26.050 --> 00:40:29.590 position:56%
This is called "Keeper of the Keys."

00:40:29.590 --> 00:40:32.970
It's dated 1740.

00:40:32.970 --> 00:40:38.120
What makes a man a
man is his good name.

00:40:38.120 --> 00:40:41.870
The rest of it is beyond
our control.

00:40:41.870 --> 00:40:46.530
Trustworthiness and honor
are riches no one can steal.

00:40:46.530 --> 00:40:53.340
Let men have faith in you,
hold true to your promise.

00:40:53.340 --> 00:41:01.120
My father's values were my sum and
substance during that cocoon year.

00:41:01.120 --> 00:41:08.850
From freedom to a new world was
one year of grief, shock, sorrow,

00:41:08.850 --> 00:41:11.380
and learning my new name

00:41:11.380 --> 00:41:16.690
and master's language,
but not master's values.

00:41:16.690 --> 00:41:20.670
Here, at least, was
something I could control.

00:41:20.670 --> 00:41:27.260
Here, there was a true essential
eye which only I could own.

00:41:27.260 --> 00:41:30.570
Here were my riches.

00:41:30.570 --> 00:41:35.460
In Barbados, the surviving
unpurchased riches were barbered,

00:41:35.460 --> 00:41:37.010
washed, and oiled.

00:41:37.010 --> 00:41:43.570 position:56%
After a year of misery and
homeward yearning, they were marched

00:41:43.570 --> 00:41:49.680
to market, sold, and given new
names, their present strength

00:41:49.680 --> 00:41:53.530
and their futures under
white control,

00:41:53.530 --> 00:41:59.390
their traditional beliefs
toppled under Christian values.

00:41:59.390 --> 00:42:05.500
I was nine years old and
filled with my father's values

00:42:05.500 --> 00:42:07.680
when we reached Rhode Island.

00:42:07.680 --> 00:42:12.430
From there, my master's
riches sailed to his home,

00:42:12.430 --> 00:42:18.300
his keys under my control, while
he disembarked for business.

00:42:18.300 --> 00:42:24.390
For a year, I had practiced,
become true virtue,

00:42:24.390 --> 00:42:27.610
bring honor to your name.

00:42:27.610 --> 00:42:33.360
Now, I promised my master his
keys would be safe with me.

00:42:33.360 --> 00:42:38.480
At master's home, his father
ordered me to give him the keys

00:42:38.480 --> 00:42:41.790
as there were some things of
value among master's thing

00:42:41.790 --> 00:42:44.110
which were purchased in his name.

00:42:44.110 --> 00:42:48.900
I told him, my master had
trusted me with his riches.

00:42:48.900 --> 00:42:52.080
I had promised to keep them safe.

00:42:52.080 --> 00:42:59.720
After a year of becoming,
I emerged, I took control.

00:43:00.770 --> 00:43:07.100
My master's father threatened, but
I controlled the keys concealed

00:43:07.100 --> 00:43:10.300
in my shirt or under
me while I slept,

00:43:10.300 --> 00:43:14.570
more watchfully than
I'd slept all year.

00:43:14.570 --> 00:43:17.670
When at last my master
unpacked his things of value,

00:43:17.670 --> 00:43:21.770
he told his father he would
trust me with all his riches

00:43:21.770 --> 00:43:27.360
because where I come from, a
man is as good as his name.

00:43:27.360 --> 00:43:33.280
What value has a man
beyond his name?

00:43:33.280 --> 00:43:35.710
Can he control his fate?

00:43:35.710 --> 00:43:38.940
Know his death year?

00:43:38.940 --> 00:43:45.510
He is richest whose
honor outlives him.

00:43:45.510 --> 00:43:52.290
[ Applause ]

00:43:52.290 --> 00:43:53.590
Thank you.

00:43:53.590 --> 00:43:58.530
I -- I just read one -- one more.

00:43:58.530 --> 00:44:01.740
The -- another persona
I've picked up is George --

00:44:01.740 --> 00:44:05.620
George Washington Carver,
and I'll just read.

00:44:05.620 --> 00:44:07.360
No, excuse me.

00:44:07.360 --> 00:44:13.510
