drop like crazy.

00:57:25.000 --> 00:57:27.010
He's like, you know, Jimmy and I --

00:57:27.010 --> 00:57:28.510
[ Laughter ]

00:57:28.510 --> 00:57:31.730
Jimmy and I -- and I'm like,
holy shit, he know Jimmy Baldwin.

00:57:31.730 --> 00:57:37.220
So I would run to the library
to find all of Addison's books

00:57:37.220 --> 00:57:39.680
and take them out and
read them and stuff.

00:57:39.680 --> 00:57:45.660
And I would -- after class, I
would go to him and he, you know,

00:57:45.660 --> 00:57:47.970
just ask him a thousand
questions, like,

00:57:47.970 --> 00:57:49.270
you know, students do to me now.

00:57:49.270 --> 00:57:54.050
And I was trying to start this
magazine once called writers --

00:57:54.050 --> 00:57:59.580
Voices of Color, and he said, Tony,
just tell me anybody you want.

00:57:59.580 --> 00:58:01.950
I know everybody.

00:58:01.950 --> 00:58:03.470
I'll get you anybody.

00:58:03.470 --> 00:58:06.340
And I just asked him, who
are your favorite poets.

00:58:06.340 --> 00:58:09.780
He said, well I like Quincy,
but he's kind of cute sometimes.

00:58:09.780 --> 00:58:12.190
And I'm like -- this poetry's
kind of cute sometimes.

00:58:12.190 --> 00:58:15.510
Whoa. So I was getting all
the -- the -- the dirt.

00:58:15.510 --> 00:58:18.710
[ Laughter ]

00:58:18.710 --> 00:58:27.460 position:56%
So, but in -- in -- in Gayle's
class, he assigned "The Black Poets"

00:58:27.460 --> 00:58:31.100
by Dudley Randall, and
that became the bible

00:58:31.100 --> 00:58:33.000
and that blew the brains out.

00:58:33.000 --> 00:58:36.330
And then that led to me
shifting to also, you know,

00:58:36.330 --> 00:58:38.710
include the Nuyorican
poets, and then the --

00:58:38.710 --> 00:58:41.150
the Central American poets,
and the African poets,

00:58:41.150 --> 00:58:43.600
and the Caribbean poets,
and on and on and on.

00:58:43.600 --> 00:58:45.520
So it's a very personal thing.

00:58:45.520 --> 00:58:49.080
I think that the Black
Arts is very foundational.

00:58:49.080 --> 00:58:52.030
It's probably the most
revolutionary,

00:58:52.030 --> 00:58:53.330
outside of the Harlem Renaissance,

00:58:53.330 --> 00:58:56.960
the most revolutionary literary
movement in our country.

00:58:56.960 --> 00:58:59.260
I talk a lot.

